## IMultiInitialState.ongoingCalls property

Determines the number of ongoing calls at the time of initialization. When set to `0`<!-- -->, no ongoing calls are happening.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
ongoingCalls: number;
```

## Remarks

If set to `0`<!-- -->, subsequent arguments for [IMultiInitialState.muted](./jabra-js.imultiinitialstate.muted.md) and [IMultiInitialState.onHold](./jabra-js.imultiinitialstate.onhold.md) will be ignored (setting mute or hold state on an idle device is not supported).
